Or does Java automatically add a new line when the System.out.print finishes? Wait, the Java code for printing is: 

for (int i=0; i <n; i++) { 

    if (i !=0)  print space, 

    print value } So the numbers are all on one line, with a space between them. So the Fortran code should also output all numbers on a single line, separated by spaces, then a newline. The way the code above writes is that each number is written with write ( with advance=yes which is the default), so each write would go to new line unless controlled.
